	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_44969303"><p>And the insurance companies are indicating that they certainly are noticing an increase in frequency and severity of adverse events, contrary to claims from the deniers.</p><p>Simulations can be terribly fiddly things, but due to wide interest, there has been a lot of work done over a period of decades to refine weather models on all time scales. It is also common to run several and compare their output, particularly for severe events like hurricanes (the weather underground shows 5 or 6 and an average with error<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
